          <div style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">♠</div>
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2" style="margin-top: 0;">Why fund managers diversify</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 0;">A pre-seed VC with genuine edge faces a Kelly fraction of around 5%. Most partners physically can't deploy 5% per cheque - their LPs demand 30+ portfolio companies, which forces each position down to 2-3%. What looks like caution is really half-Kelly dressed up as diversification policy. Kelly explains the shape of venture portfolio construction in one number.</p>
